claim.claim-text:
18. A method of using a soil aerator system to form an aeration pocket, comprising:
moving a soil aerator system over a patch of soil, the soil aerator system comprising at least one aeration tine coupled to a tine holder member, the aeration tine having a curved knife portion and an aeration tube coupled to the curved knife portion and spaced apart from a tip portion;
penetrating the patch of soil with the tip portion of the aeration tine;
fracturing the soil with the curved knife portion; and
removing a soil plug with the aeration tube.
